<div class="container">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div id="comments-5">
        
            <article id="comment-782">
              <time datetime="2011-05-02">May 02, 2011</time>
              <p>Ive been coming to your resturants since you first opened on Wardour St. I still frequent as much as possible, and love the calamari with chilli sauce, Mmmm... I thik i might just have to try your new Westfield opening today!</p>
              <p class="author">From William</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-778">
              <time datetime="2011-05-01">May 01, 2011</time>
              <p>This is my favorite restuarant in london. The food is incredible. Gong Tohd prawns :)</p>
              <p class="author">From Chelsey</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-766">
              <time datetime="2011-04-19">April 19, 2011</time>
              <p>You're the perfect restaurant when I can't think of anything I would like to eat OR when I crave for lots of things at the same time! I also like my regular spot, sitting at the window, peoplewatching in Wardour Street. Every once in a while I try a new dish. Never disappointing. My favs are the chicken wings (biceps more like it) and the grilled chicken noodles, with a satay or curry sauce on the side.</p>

<p>One question though: where can I buy those fabulous glasses? They really add to the experience of eating your food.</p>

<p>And let's not forget your staff. Always friendly, always in for a joke.</p>
              <p class="author">From Marcel</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-750">
              <time datetime="2011-04-10">April 10, 2011</time>
              <p>One of the best Thai restaurants in London! Absolutely love their green curry... Can never get enough of it! Hats off to the chef</p>
              <p class="author">From Priyanka Sharma</p>
    
            </article>


            <article id="comment-738">
              <time datetime="2011-04-04">April 04, 2011</time>
              <p>Had dinner at the Bird Street restaurant last Friday, the food was amazing, I would definitely recommend the calamari and char-grilled duck. Best meal I've had in a long time and the service was excellent, really friendly and knowledge waiters and their recommendations went down a treat!</p>
              <p class="author">From Neil Sadiq</p>
    
            </article>

